[The USA, India, and Brazil are still the most severely affected countries in terms of cumulative case counts and daily new case confirmations, with India now in the 2nd position followed by Brazil. In the past 24 hours, these 3 countries -- India (81 911), followed by the USA (40 831) and Brazil (19 089) -- account for over half of all confirmed cases globally (54.4%) and 55.5% of all newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours. A global total of 4382 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (13-14 Sep 2020).

Countries reporting more than 5000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours include India, USA, Brazil, Spain (17 033), Argentina (9909), France (6158), Colombia (5573), and Russia (5509), and 29 countries have reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours. 7 of the top 20 countries reporting the highest daily newly confirmed cases are from the Americas region and 7 are from the European region. Spain reported the 4th highest daily cases globally today and on 11 Sep 2020.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, there is an increase in case counts by 5.4%, while daily reported deaths have decreased by 14.9%.

Impression: Cases are increasing globally, with Europe showing major increasing transmission in many countries. - Mod.MPP]
